Herman Mashaba delivers his party manifesto for the upcoming local government elections at the Old Park Station in Johannesburg, on September 22, 2021. JOHANNESBURG -  ActionSA president Herman Mashaba has resigned as a City of Johannesburg councillor. READ: ActionSA vows action against members who disrupted meeting According to Mashaba, he wants to focus on expanding ActionSA nationwide. He also says it is time for someone else to gain local government experience.   President @HermanMashaba has officially announced his resignation as a Johannesburg Councillor in order to focus his efforts on growing ActionSA across the length and breadth of South Africa, so that we can unseat the ANC in 2024. https://t.co/58S9FgQwnw ActionSA Press Statement - Mashaba to Step Back as City of Johannesburg Councillor. Immediate Release by eNews Channel Africa on Scribd 